text: Wen Tzu-yun (born 29 September 1993) is a Taiwanese karateka. She is a two- time gold medalist in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the Asian Games and a two-time bronze medalist in this event at the World Karate Championships. She won the gold medal at the Asian Games both in 2014 and in 2018. She is scheduled to represent Chinese Taipei at the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo, Japan in karate. At the 2017 World Games held in Wrocław, Poland, she won the silver medal in the women's kumite 55 kg event.
